<h1>Cuprocyparis leylandii</h1>

<h2>How to pronounce</h2>

<p>Cu-pro-cyparis</p>

<h2>Common Name</h2>

<p>Leyland cypress</p>

<h2>Description</h2>

<p>A large, fast-growing, dense conifer of columnar habit which can reach heights in excess of 30m if unchecked. Its dense foliage forms flattened, slightly drooping sprays of scale-like leaves.</p>

